      "content": "That \"drag\" on your payments can be attributed to another factor: fees. Many student loans come with origination fees, which are charges added to the loan when it's first issued. These fees can be a percentage of the loan amount, and they can reduce the amount of principal that's paid each month. It's like a small, sneaky tax that's taking away from your hard-earned money.\n\nAdditionally, some loans may also have late payment fees, which can add to the overall interest and principal amount. These fees can be a real \"goblin in the weeds,\" making it seem like your money is disappearing before it even reaches the principal balance.",
